			About Clal Group
		




Print



















Clal Insurance Enterprises Holdings Ltd 
Line of Business - Insurance and long-term savings, including non-life insurance, health insurance, pension and provident funds for private and corporate customers. Established in 1987
Clal Insurance Enterprises Holdings Ltd. Group is part of the IDB Group, which owns 55% of its shares. Bank Hapoalim holds 10%, with the rest held by the public and traded on the Tel-Aviv Stock Exchange. In terms of gross premium, the Group holds a 18% share of the insurance market and manages 1.6 billion NIS worth of assets (updated for the end of 2015).
Clal Insurance Enterprises Holdings is rated A by Standard & Poor's Maalot. The group owns insurance agencies, pension funds, provident funds and study funds. The group employs 4,200 people and collaborates with 1,800 insurance agents. These activities position Clal as one of Israel's leading insurance, pension, and financial services groups.
Long-Term Saving 
The Life Insurance and Long-Term Saving Division provides comprehensive solutions for private and corporate customers in all sectors of the economy.Clal Insurance Group holds a 15% market share of Israel`s long-term savings market, as defined by the Commissioner of Insurance. The Group's pension funds manage assets worth over 48 Billion NIS for 690,000 members, while its provident funds manage 35 Billion NIS (updated for the end of 2015).Within its profit-sharing life insurance activity, the group holds a 21% market share in terms of assets, with a total annual premium volume of approximately 5 billion NIS (in 2015). Clal Insurance takes full responsibility for managing its member’s funds. Members enjoy high returns, among the highest in the Israeli market, as well as peace of mind, knowing a large, professional, industry-leading corporation manages their money.
Non-Life Insurance
Clal Insurance Group is one of the leading non-life insurance companies in Israel, with an annual premium of 2.5 Billion NIS (in 2015). The company offers a wide range of insurance plans for private and corporate customers in the automotive, home, property, etc., while professionally understanding the unique needs of its diverse customers.  
Health Insurance
The Health Division manages annual premiums totaling 1.7 Billion NIS (in 2015). The company offers its customers diverse private health insurance plans, nursing insurance, travel insurance and more. Its private health insurance portfolio allows members to choose the right coverage for their needs, while providing correct pricing and professional assistance, based on the trends and changes in the industry and in accordance with them.
 
Investments
Canaf, the group`s investment arm, manages assets worth more than 168 Billion NIS (updated for the end of 2015), including members` pension funds, provident funds, insurance executives and also Clal`s balance sheet assets and insurance reserves.
Service and Innovation
Clal is committed to constantly improve the service it provides to its customers and its agents and thus is leading a service revolution, based on innovative new digital tools, obtaining im-mediate service from anywhere, anytime. As part of this concept, Clal launched the Clal On-Line application, which allows its insurance agents produce on-line policy in just minutes, the Clal Info service, which allows agents to send and receive information and instant updates via SMS and e-mail and know in real time about their customers` service processes - and many additional innovative services.
 










  











